Lesothoâ€™s central bank will issue
three- and five-year treasury bonds with coupon rates of 8.25
percent and 9 percent respectively, the central bank said in an
e-mailed statement today.  The central bank in the capital, Maseru, will sell 25
million maloti ($3.6 million) of three-year bonds and 37 million
maloti of five-year bonds on Dec. 8. It will accept minimum
competitive bids of 100,000 maloti and non-competitive bids of
5,000 maloti.  To contact the reporter on this story:
